timeline.bodyText:
Isn't this count misleading? While parameterCount contains the individual params including the included record params, invokableSymbol.includedRecordParams contains all the fields from the individual included record params, the sum is therefore more than the actual param count.
The following doesn't fail atm
type Options record {|
    string name;
|};

function foo(int id, *Options options) {
    string? name = options?.name; // "baz" is set
}

public function main() {
    foo(1, name = "bar", options = {name: "baz"}); // `name` is passed as an individual named arg as well as via `options`
}

